The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Hind Motors back in black

 OUR BUREAU

 Jan. 29: Hindustan Motors has posted a net profit of Rs 1.76 crore in the third quarter ended December compared with a loss of Rs 29.82 crore in the corresponding previous period.

 Net sales grew 47.79 per cent to Rs 242.72 crore against Rs 164.23 crore.

 In the nine months to December, the company suffered a loss of Rs 27.62 crore, down from Rs 82.19 crore in the corresponding period last year.

 Net sales grew 32 per cent to Rs 658.80 crore against Rs 497.32 crore in the year-ago period.

 The profit in the third quarter has largely been attributed to the foray into new lines of businesses such as supply of power to General Motors India.

Berger plant

 Berger Paints India will acquire a paints plant in Russia, which will be a wholly-owned subsidiary of the company. 

 ?The board has authorised investment in an overseas company, which will be a wholly-owned subsidiary, for setting up a paints manufacturing unit in Russia,? the company said.

 The company announced a 26 per cent increase in net profit to Rs 15.22 crore during the quarter ended December from Rs 12.09 crore, while net sales increased 29 per cent to Rs 257.94 crore from Rs 199.27 crore.




